					<!--cached-Fri, 18 Jul 2014 16:11:48 +0000-->Taipo, i have similar to popsel&#39;s problem with russian language. Function scrubster() filters out all non-latin symbols. All russian symbols is non-latin. The workaround (for me) is:<br /><br />find<br /><pre class='prettyprint lang-auto linenums:0'>preg_replace(&quot;/&#91;^ a-zA-Z0-9?=@%:{}&#092;/_.-&#93;/i&quot;, &quot;&quot;, urldecode( &#036;nodes ) );</pre>replace with<br /><pre class='prettyprint lang-auto linenums:0'>preg_replace(&quot;/&#91;^ a-zA-Z--0-9?=@%:{}&#092;/_.-&#93;/i&quot;, &quot;&quot;, urldecode( &#036;nodes ) );</pre><br />Can u see the difference? Is your browser correctly display cyrilic symbols?
					
